description: This Java class defines the Product entity for a backend application, including its properties, database mappings, constructors, and getter/setter methods.

classes.name: Product
classes.description: Entity representing a product with fields like SKU, name, description, and image URL, mapped to the 'products' database table.

methods.name: getId
methods.description: Returns the unique identifier of the product.

methods.name: getSku
methods.description: Returns the SKU of the product.

methods.name: setSku
methods.description: Sets the SKU of the product.

methods.name: getName
methods.description: Returns the name of the product.

methods.name: setName
methods.description: Sets the name of the product.

methods.name: getDescription
methods.description: Returns the description of the product.

methods.name: setDescription
methods.description: Sets the description of the product.

methods.name: getImageUrl
methods.description: Returns the image URL of the product.

methods.name: setImageUrl
methods.description: Sets the image URL of the product.
